				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4057658/scp-3552#post-3619740</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 25 Oct 2017 15:13:47 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Lackwit</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>616788</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I quite like it, but you describe the tumors as being composed of fruit &quot;sinew&quot;, which is a word normally only applied to tough animal connective tissue or cartilage&#8212;&quot;pith&quot; (which describes tough fibrous tissue in plants and fruits) might be a better choice, in my opinion.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
